CAPE TOWN, October 27  – Former South African president FW de Klerk was admitted to Panorama Hospital in Cape Town on Friday with a condition known as pneumothorax, the FW de Klerk Foundation said on Saturday. Pneumothorax is an abnormal collection of air in the pleural space between the lung and the chest wall, the foundation said in a statement on Saturday. De Klerk, 82, underwent a successful procedure on Saturday morning and was expected to be discharged from hospital some time next week, the foundation said in a brief statement posted on its website.(ANA) 